HEADWORD: Discordancy
<hw>Dis*cord"an*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>discordance</ets>.]</ety> <def>State or quality of being
discordant; disagreement; inconsistency.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There will arise a thousand <qex>discordances</qex> of
opinion.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discordant</ent>⟦br⟧
